# Step 2: Install Dependencies 

### Ok, now let's install everything we need to start recognizin' faces. Riffing off a pretty solid tutorial from [PiMyLifeUp](pimylifeup.com/raspberry-pi-opencv/) with some modifications, as some things are out of date. 

### Ok, diving in:

1. Dependencies to install

```
sudo apt install cmake build-essential pkg-config git
```
```
sudo apt install libjpeg-dev libtiff-dev libjasper-dev libpng-dev libwebp-dev libopenexr-dev
```
```
sudo apt install libavcodec-dev libavformat-dev libswscale-dev libv4l-dev libxvidcore-dev libx264-dev libdc1394-22-dev libgstreamer-plugins-base1.0-dev libgstreamer1.0-dev
```
```
sudo apt-get install libqt5gui5 libqt5webkit5 libqt5test5
```
```
sudo apt install libatlas-base-dev liblapacke-dev gfortran
```
```
sudo apt install libhdf5-dev libhdf5-103
```
```
sudo apt install python3-dev python3-pip python3-numpy
```
